reviews.text: A small veggie cafe. Love the veggie food here. Burger, salad are personal favorite. No choice over daily soup but so far all are fine to me. Organic Soya milk or Pukka tea come with the set meal . No coffee available . May be kitchen not big enough to offer too many options.
Good idea to use veggie only to do spaghetti carbonara , taste ok but it's not similar at all

Good little place in a food court. Burger was nice (though a tad small), staff was friendly. I would go again, but you've gotta be in the neighborhood, which is not exactly the center of the universe.
Just the best veggie food 😘
Completely vegan and delicious! For $97 I had a beverage, salad, soup and entree. Yummy yummy. It's a small spot inside a food arcade, must try!

result.formatted_address: 7 Shing Yip St, Kwun Tong, Hong Kong
result.name: E-Plaza

reviews.text: Full of restaurants, mostly unique and only a few chain stores.

Lots of food varieties and above all inexpensive.  Seating is limited and not quite comfortable.  Ideal for quick eat prior to outlet shopping.  Why prior?  Shops do not welcome guests coming in with luggage's and many bags.  Shop floor space is a premium in Hong Kong.
Small shopping mall. Ideal place for quick meals
At least five vegan/ vegetarian restaurants found on the first floor of this plaza. Chinese, western, Japanese, you name it 👍🏻👍🏻

Convenient location, near Kwun Tong station only ten minutes, in the ground floor like a food street. 
You can find some kind of Japanese, Taiwan, Chinese & western restaurants in there and the food price is acceptable.
